				\begin{document}$$I_{{\mathrm{CO}}_2}$$\end{document}ICO2 remains a valid emission factor that can be used to calculate annual emissions. The OS plant statistics19 support the assumption of a constant product mixture as it varies by <10% month to month. Finally, the possibility of unforeseen facility maintenance, open burning of overburden, or increased flaring resulting in increased CO2 emissions cannot be ruled out. However, there was no evidence of maintenance or burning occurring during this study, and flaring is expected to account for a very small fraction of the overall CO2 emissions. Regardless, such events are unlikely to have occurred systematically across the exact days of study during the months of August and September.
